1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a department of transportation study regarding autonomous and
2 semiautonomous vehicle technologies; and to provide a legislative management report.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION STUDY - AUTONOMOUS AND
5 SEMIAUTONOMOUS VEHICLE TECHNOLOGIES - REPORT TO LEGISLATIVE
6 MANAGEMENT.
7 1. During the 2025-26 interim, the department of transportation shall study relevant
8 issues in order to develop a preemptive regulatory and statutory framework for the
9 operation of autonomous and semiautonomous vehicles on the North Dakota highway
10 system. The study must include:
11 a. A process for determining where the state's infrastructure may or may not be fully
12 prepared for widespread deployment of autonomous and semiautonomous
13 vehicle technologies;
14 b. A process to review accident and traffic data for autonomous and
15 semiautonomous vehicle systems with independent oversight on the industry
16 operators;
17 c. If there is a need to promulgate rules relating to accident liability regarding
18 autonomous and semiautonomous vehicle technologies; and
19 d. A determination of common vulnerabilities relating to privacy concerns and data
20 security with proposed solutions.
